Short Title: GSC Advance Health Care Planning Documents. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Davis.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MODIFY THE GENERAL STATUTES REGARDING HEALTH CARE
3 POWERS OF ATTORNEY, ADVANCE HEALTH CARE DIRECTIVES, AND
4 ADVANCE INSTRUCTIONS FOR MENTAL HEALTH TREATMENT BASED, IN
5 PART, ON PROPOSALS IN THE UNIFORM HEALTH-CARE DECISIONS ACT, AS
6 RECOMMENDED BY THE GENERAL STATUTES COMMISSION.
7 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
8
9 PART I. FINDINGS
10 SECTION 1. The General Statutes Commission, pursuant to its charge under
11 G.S. 164-13, finds that the adoption of certain proposals in the 2023 Uniform Health-Care
12 Decisions Act would improve the laws of this State. Among these proposals is simplifying
13 execution requirements for health care powers of attorney, advance health care directives ("living
14 wills"), and advance instructions for mental health treatment.
15 The Commission further finds that House Bill 349, 2025 Regular Session, would
16 simplify execution requirements for health care powers of attorney and advance health care
17 directives ("living wills"), two of the three documents for which the General Statutes
18 Commission recommends simplifying execution requirements. In addition to making technical
19 corrections, this act in its entirety provides for all recommendations of the General Statutes
20 Commission resulting from its consideration of the 2023 Uniform Health-Care Decisions Act.
21 Parts II and III of this act would ensure the enactment of all of the Commission's
22 recommendations if House Bill 349 does or does not become law.
23
