2 This document gives the person you designate as your health care agent broad powers to make
3 health care decisions for you when you cannot make the decision yourself or cannot communicate
4 your decision to other people. You should discuss your wishes concerning life-prolonging
5 measures, mental health treatment, and other health care decisions with your health care agent.
6 Except to the extent that you express specific limitations or restrictions in this form, your health
7 care agent may make any health care decision you could make yourself.
8
9 This form does not impose a duty on your health care agent to exercise granted powers, but when
10 a power is exercised, your health care agent will be obligated to use due care to act in your best
11 interests and in accordance with this document.
12
13 This Health Care Power of Attorney form is intended to be valid in any jurisdiction in which it
14 is presented, but places outside North Carolina may impose requirements that this form does not
15 meet.
16
17 If you want to use this form, you must complete it, sign it, and have your signature witnessed by
18 two qualified witnesses and or proved by a notary public. Follow the instructions about which
19 choices you can initial very carefully. Do not sign this form until two witnesses and or a notary
20 public are present to watch you sign it. You then should give a copy to your health care agent
21 and to any alternates you name. You should consider filing it with the Advance Health Care
22 Directive Registry maintained by the North Carolina Secretary of State:
23 http://www.nclifelinks.org/ahcdr/State.
24 …
