13 ADVANCE DIRECTIVE FOR A NATURAL DEATH ("LIVING WILL")
14
15 NOTE: YOU SHOULD USE THIS DOCUMENT TO GIVE YOUR HEALTH CARE
16 PROVIDERS INSTRUCTIONS TO WITHHOLD OR WITHDRAW
17 LIFE-PROLONGING MEASURES IN CERTAIN SITUATIONS. THERE IS NO LEGAL
18 REQUIREMENT THAT ANYONE EXECUTE A LIVING WILL.
19
20 GENERAL INSTRUCTIONS: You can use this Advance Directive ("Living Will") form to give
21 instructions for the future if you want your health care providers to withhold or withdraw
22 life-prolonging measures in certain situations. You should talk to your doctor about what these
23 terms mean. The Living Will states what choices you would have made for yourself if you were
24 able to communicate. Talk to your family members, friends, and others you trust about your
25 choices. Also, it is a good idea to talk with professionals such as your doctors, clergypersons,
26 and lawyers before you complete and sign this Living Will.
27
28 You do not have to use this form to give those instructions, but if you create your own Advance
29 Directive you need to be very careful to ensure that it is consistent with North Carolina law.
30
31 This Living Will form is intended to be valid in any jurisdiction in which it is presented, but places
32 outside North Carolina may impose requirements that this form does not meet.
33
34 If you want to use this form, you must complete it, sign it, and have your signature witnessed by
35 two qualified witnesses and or proved by a notary public. Follow the instructions about which
